name: FAMICOM / FAMILY COMPUTER
description: Japan, 1983, the Nintendo launched the Famicom or the Family Computer.  It’s An 8 bits console with cartridges. Its was design to make it look like a toy and had controllers that were totally differents from the  standards of this time. The 8 bits console was later redesigned to be released on the North America as we know as the NES.
